gy."])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"67:[\"$\",\"div\",\"2585-purport,2585-purport\",{\"className\":\"av-purport\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4\",\"children\":\"Purport\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-2590\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:3:child_items:4:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"The Supreme Personality of Godhead is not perceivable through the gross material senses. It is said,\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-2591\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:3:child_items:4:children:1\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-center italic\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"\u003cem\u003eataḥ śrī-kṛṣṇa-nāmādi\u003cbr /\u003ena bhaved grāhyam indriyaiḥ\u003cbr /\u003esevonmukhe hi jihvādau\u003cbr /\u003esvayam eva sphuraty adaḥ\u003c/em\u003e\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-2592\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:3:child_items:4:children:2\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-right\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"(\u003cem\u003eBhakti-rasāmṛta-sindhu\u003c/em\u003e 1.2.234)\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-2593\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:3:child_items:4:children:3\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$108\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-2594\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:3:child_items:4:children:4\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"Yet one should not conclude that because He is spread all over He has lost His personal existence. To refute such an argument the Lord says, “I am everywhere, and everything is in Me, but still I am aloof.” For example, a king heads a government which is but the manifestation of the king’s energy; the different governmental departments are nothing but the energies of the king, and each department is resting on the king’s power. But still one cannot expect the king to be present in every department personally. That is a crude example. Similarly, all the manifestations that we see and everything that exists, both in this material world and in the spiritual world, are resting on the energy of the Supreme Personality of Godhead. The creation takes place by the diffusion of His different energies, and, as stated in the \u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā, viṣṭabhyāham idaṁ kṛtsnam:\u003c/em\u003e He is everywhere present by His personal representation, the diffusion of His different energies.\"}}]}]]]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"68:[\"$\",\"div\",\"2595-devanagari,2595-devanagari\",{\"className\":\"av-devanagari\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Devanagari\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-2596\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:4:child_items:0:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-lg text-center\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"न च मत्स्थानि भूतानि पश्य मे योगमैश्वरम् ।\u003cbr/\u003eभूतभृन्न च भूतस्थो ममात्मा भूतभावन: ॥ ५ ॥\"}}]}]]]}]\n69:[\"$\",\"div\",\"2595-verse_text,2595-verse_text\",{\"className\":\"av-verse_text\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidde