y along with the universe. Men, animals, beasts, birds – everything is simultaneously created, because whatever desires the living entities had at the last annihilation are again manifested. It is clearly indicated here by the word \u003cem\u003eavaśam\u003c/em\u003e that the living entities have nothing to do with this process. The state of being in their past life in the past creation is simply manifested again, and all this is done simply by His will. This is the inconceivable potency of the Supreme Personality of God. And after creating different species of life, He has no connection with them. The creation takes place to accommodate the inclinations of the various living entities, and so the Lord does not become involved with it.7b:[\"$\",\"div\",\"2617-purport,2617-purport\",{\"className\":\"av-purport\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4\",\"children\":\"Purport\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-2622\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:pro"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"ps:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:7:child_items:4:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"This material world is the manifestation of the inferior energy of the Supreme Personality of Godhead. This has already been explained several times. At the creation, the material energy is let loose as the \u003cem\u003emahat-tattva,\u003c/em\u003e into which the Lord as His first \u003cem\u003epuruṣa\u003c/em\u003e incarnation, Mahā-viṣṇu, enters. He lies within the Causal Ocean and breathes out innumerable universes, and into each universe the Lord again enters as Garbhodaka-śāyī Viṣṇu. Each universe is in that way created. He still further manifests Himself as Kṣīrodaka-śāyī Viṣṇu, and that Viṣṇu enters into everything – even into the minute atom. This fact is explained here. He enters into everything.\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-2623\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:7:child_items:4:children:1\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$10a\"}}]}]]]}]\n7c:[\"$\",\"div\",\"2624-devanagari,2624-devanagari\",{\"className\":\"av-devanagari\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Devanagari\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-2625\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:8:child_items:0:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-lg text-center\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"न च मां तानि कर्माणि निबध्‍नन्ति धनञ्जय ।\u003cbr/\u003eउदासीनवदासीनमसक्तं तेषु कर्मसु ॥ ९ ॥\"}}]}]]]}]\n7d:[\"$\",\"div\",\"2624-verse_text,2624-verse_text\",{\"className\":\"av-verse_text\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 "])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Verse text\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-2626\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:8:child_items:1:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-center italic\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"\u003cem\u003ena ca māṁ tāni karmāṇi\u003cbr /\u003enibadhnanti dhanañ-jaya\u003cbr /\u003eudāsīna-vad āsīnam\u003cbr /\u003easaktaṁ teṣu karmasu\u003c/em\u003e\"}}]}]]]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"7e:[\"$\",\"div\",\"2624-synonyms,2624-synonyms\",{\"className\":\"av-synonyms\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4\",\"children\":\"Synonyms\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L53\",\"child-26